    {
        "content": "<p>macovedj opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13891\">PR #13891</a> from <code>macovedj:dropped-stream-bug</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>When guest streams receive <code>StreamResult::Dropped</code> on their first poll (like would occur when hitting EOF), wasmtime is failing to transition from <code>ReadState::HostReady</code>/<code>WriteState::HostReady</code> to <code>Dropped</code>, so the host <code>StreamProducer</code>/<code>StreamConsumer</code> is never dropped and its completion future never resolves, leaving guest awaits hung.</p>\n<p>This PR checks for <code>Dropped</code> and transitions when this occurs, in the same fashion as <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/main/crates/wasmtime/src/runtime/component/concurrent/futures_and_streams.rs#L2350\">pipe_to_guest</a> and <code>pipe_from_guest</code> already do today.</p>\n<p>I created a little repro repo <a href=\"https://github.com/macovedj/wasmtime-stream-repo\">here</a> that reproduces the hang and runs clean with these changes.<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 611158387,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1784233310
    },
