    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13891#discussion_r3604907018\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Similar to above could this be refactored with <code>pipe_to_guest</code> to reduce duplication?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 611335942,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1784308420
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13891#discussion_r3604904035\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The handling here is I believe a duplicate (mostly) of <code>pipe_from_guest</code> where that function handles the dropped case and this function previously didn't but now does. Would you be up for a refactor to extract the \"move the state forward after an event function\" to be shared between here and <code>pipe_from_guest</code>? That way there'd in theory be less duplication and less chance this proves an issue in the future</p>\n</blockquote>",
